# Bitstream dual-runtime parity (UART / Simulation, dev / VSIX)

**NON-NEGOTIABLE:** Every Bitstream-related feature must behave correctly in **both** telemetry backends and ship the same in **dev** and **installed VSIX**.

## UART and Simulation

Treat **UART** (serial / BS-framed firmware) and **Simulation** (external **bitstream-simulator** VS Code extension) as **first-class peers**.

- Backend store: **`uart`** (UI **Bitstream**) | **`simulator`** — no Auto mode.
- **Ingest:** **`shouldIngestTelemetry()`** — Simulator ingests BS2 from external sim; UART only when serial is open.
- See **`extension/HOW_TO_RUN.md`** for bridge + sim install.

## VS Code webview detection

- **Do not** use **`T3DVSCodeUtils.isVsCodeMode()` alone**.
- **Use** **`isVsCodeExtensionWebview()`**, **`window.WEBVIEW_READY`**, **`window.__VSCODE_API__`**.

## Build

- **`npm run compile`** in **`extension/`** before packaging.
- Re-test **`.vsix`** in a clean window after **`npm run package`**.

